Download Docker -----> yum install docker -y
Start Docker -------->systemctl start docker 
Enable Docker ------->systemctl enable docker
What is Docker version--> docker --version
docker info
For more help ------->docker container --help
How many running container --> docker container ls
View Stop/Running containers -----> docker container ls -a
create container and deploy image ---> docker container run ubuntu
Run container in Background/Detached mode ----> docker container run -d ubuntu sleep 50 (It will close after 50 seconds)
Interactive mode, (container will keep running) ----> docker container run -d -it ubuntu
Stop ---> docker container stop + container ID
Start ----> docker container start + container ID
Restart ----> docker container restart + container ID
Remove ----> docker container rm + container ID
You cannot remove running container --> Stop container and remove or remove force fully
Force Full Remove ----> docker container rm + container ID -f
Create container and Go inside Container -----> docker container run -it ubuntu /bin/bash
Find IP for Container --- > docker container inspect + container ID
Curl http:// + IP address
Docker container run -it ubuntu /bin/bash
Apt git update
Apt git install pache2 -y
Cd /var/html
Echo “Welcome to my docker page” > index.html
Docker apace to start
